{"id": "ambiguous-004", "question": "How do I secure my Kubernetes cluster?", "golden_answer": "The question is ambiguous — security has many dimensions: authentication (who can access the API server?), authorization (RBAC), network policy (Pod-to-Pod traffic), Pod security standards (privilege constraints), Secrets handling, image supply-chain trust, runtime threat detection, and node hardening. Each is a separate topic with its own docs. The system should ask which security layer is the focus.", "expected_source_files": [], "type": "ambiguous"}
{"id": "ambiguous-005", "question": "What should I monitor in my cluster?", "golden_answer": "The question is ambiguous — 'monitoring' covers many distinct concerns: control-plane health (API server latency, etcd consistency), Node-level resource usage (CPU, memory, disk), workload metrics (Pod CPU, request rates, error rates), and event/log aggregation. Each requires different tools and metrics. The system should ask which layer of the stack is the focus.", "expected_source_files": [], "type": "ambiguous"}
